fields.description:
This is an improvement to GHC-105.  While the data is now stored and happy in AO, the old references still lurk in JIRA's database and have the potential to still affect performance.  We've successfully run the following SQL directly on affected databases and after a restart the affected JIRA projects are running fast:

{code:SQL}
DELETE FROM propertytext WHERE id IN (SELECT id FROM propertyentry WHERE property_key ILIKE '%IssueCommitArray%');
DELETE FROM propertyentry WHERE property_key ILIKE '%IssueCommitArray%';
{code}
*always take a database backup before performing direct database manipulation

If it's possible, it would be great if the plugin could handle this sort of thing in an upgrade task.
